- 'Available sizes' refer to the sizes of clothing items that are listed in the inventory;
- 'Ordered sizes' refer to the sizes of clothing items that customers have actually ordered;
- 'Order count' is the number of times a specific size of a clothing item has been ordered.

- 'Top 5 customers' refers to the customers with the highest total spending on clothing items;
- 'Specific brands' are the brands from which the customers have made purchases;
- 'Chest measurements for the sizes they ordered' refers to the chest measurement values corresponding to the sizes of the clothing items that were ordered.

- 'priciest gem' refers to the most expensive item in the order;
- 'treasure chest' is a metaphor for an order placed by a customer;
- 'golden key' is a metaphor for customer_id = 1.

- "patrons of the fashion world" refers to customers who have made purchases;
- "labels they have embraced" refers to the brands of clothing items they have ordered;
- "in the realm of delivered garments" means the orders have been marked as 'delivered'.

- 'stands out as the most valuable gem' refers to the brand with the highest average order value;
- 'shining with an average order value' refers to the calculated average of the total value of orders for each item (price * quantity);
- 'surpasses the $50 threshold' refers to the condition where the average order value is greater than 50.

- 'towering figures' refers to customers with a high average height;
- 'invested in their elegance' refers to the total amount spent on formal clothing items;
- 'ledger of our stylish emporium' refers to the database of customer orders and measurements.

- "recent orders" refers to orders placed in the near past;
- "specific measurements" include details like the measurement name, value, and unit for each clothing item;
- "ordered by the most recent and highest total amounts first" means the results are sorted by order date in descending order and then by total amount in descending order.

- 'cumulative count of clothing items' refers to the total number of items ordered by customers over time;
- 'latest cumulative count' refers to the most recent total count as of the latest order date;
- 'brand and gender' are used to categorize the orders, similar to different sections in a garden.

- "Woven gold" refers to customers who have spent a significant amount of money;
- "Cumulative cost" is the total sum of all orders made by each customer;
- "Weavers" are the customers;
- "Woven wealth" represents the cumulative order cost.

- "fashion gems" are items of clothing that are considered valuable or desirable;
- "shining on the shelf" refers to items that are currently available in stock;
- "modest $50.00 and a more luxurious $200.00" are the price ranges for the clothing items.

- "favorite brand" refers to the brand of the top-selling item for each customer;
- "most frequently ordered item" is determined by the total quantity of the item ordered;
- "received" implies the order status is either 'shipped' or 'delivered'.

- "Generous patrons" refers to customers who have made significant purchases;
- "Luxurious garments" refers to clothing items produced by Brand Y;
- "Brand Y" corresponds to the brand with `brand_id` 1 in the database.

- 'accumulated the greatest treasure of discounts' refers to the maximum cumulative discount received by each customer;
- 'their most valuable haul' refers to the highest cumulative discount for each customer;
- 'delivered orders' are orders that have been successfully delivered to the customer.

- 'sought-after size' refers to the size that has been ordered the most;
- 'wardrobe of SpecificBrandName' refers to the collection of clothing items produced by the brand 'SpecificBrandName';
- 'men and women' refers to the gender categories for which the clothing items are intended.

- 'Wardrobe of fashion' refers to the collection of clothing items available in the database;
- 'Patrons' refers to the customers who have placed orders;
- 'Chosen by the patrons' means the items that have been included in orders;
- 'Measurements across their shoulders' refers to the 'across shoulder' measurement value for the items;
- 'Catalogued by the style they embody and the size they are tailored to' means the items are grouped by their style and size;
- 'Listed in alphabetical order, with their chosen sizes following suit' means the results are ordered by customer name and then by order size.

sql:
SELECT SUM(total_amount) AS total_spent_on_pending_orders
FROM orders
WHERE order_date = '2023-05-02' AND status = 'pending';
